## Instructions
1. Clean `categories_cleaned`: remove Wikipedia maintenance categories, stubs, and meta-categories.
2. Build `topic_hierarchy` from broad to specific (e.g. ["Science", "Computer Science", "Machine Learning"]).
3. Assign `domain` as a single primary domain (e.g. "computer_science", "history", "biology").
4. Extract `subject_tags`: 3-12 topical tags derived from categories and content.

## Output Format
JSON only:
{
  "categories_cleaned": ["string"],
  "topic_hierarchy": ["string"],
  "domain": "string|null",
  "subject_tags": ["string"]
}
